## 🧪 Local Testing Workflow

### 1. Start All Services

```bash
# Terminal 1: PocketBase (Database/API)
cd pocketbase/local
pocketbase serve

# Terminal 2: Bridge Service (OBS Controller)
cd sanctuary-bridge
npm run dev

# Terminal 3: Tauri App (Frontend)
cd sanctuary-app
npm run tauri dev

# Terminal 4: OBS Studio
# Start OBS manually with WebSocket enabled
# Tools → WebSocket Server Settings → Enable
```

### 2. Environment Files

**`sanctuary-bridge/.env`** (Local):
```bash
PB_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8090
BRIDGE_EMAIL=bridge@local.dev
BRIDGE_PASS=bridge123
OBS_URL=ws://127.0.0.1:4455
OBS_PASS=your-obs-password
STREAM_ID=<from schema init output>
LOG_LEVEL=debug
NODE_ENV=development
```

**`sanctuary-app/.env`** (Local):
```bash
VITE_PB_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8090
```

### 3. Mock OBS (No OBS Required)

For testing without OBS, create a mock server:

```bash
# sanctuary-bridge/scripts/mock-obs.js
const WebSocket = require('ws');

const wss = new WebSocket.Server({ port: 4455 });

wss.on('connection', (ws) => {
  console.log('Mock OBS: Client connected');

  ws.on('message', (data) => {
    const msg = JSON.parse(data);
    console.log('Mock OBS: Received', msg);

    // Respond with success
    ws.send(JSON.stringify({
      op: 7,
      d: {
        requestType: msg.d.requestType,
        requestId: msg.d.requestId,
        requestStatus: { result: true, code: 100 }
      }
    }));
  });

  // Send Identified message
  ws.send(JSON.stringify({
    op: 2,
    d: { negotiatedRpcVersion: 1 }
  }));
});

console.log('Mock OBS WebSocket server running on ws://127.0.0.1:4455');
```

```bash
# Run mock OBS
node sanctuary-bridge/scripts/mock-obs.js

# Update .env
OBS_URL=ws://127.0.0.1:4455
OBS_PASS=any-password
```

### 4. Test Full Flow

```bash
# 1. Open Tauri app (http://localhost:1420 or native window)
# 2. Login as pastor@local.dev / pastor123
# 3. Click "Begin Mass" button
# 4. Check Bridge logs:
cd sanctuary-bridge
npm run dev
# Should see: "✅ Command executed: START"

# 5. Verify in PocketBase Admin UI:
# http://127.0.0.1:8090/_/
# Collections → commands → Last record should have executed=true
```

