## 🌍 Environment Management

### Configuration Files

```
.env.example           # Template (committed to Git)
.env                   # Local dev (gitignored)
.env.local            # Local overrides (gitignored)
.env.staging          # Staging config (gitignored)
.env.production       # Production config (gitignored, stored in secrets manager)
```

### Environment-Specific Values

```bash
# .env (Local)
PB_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8090
NODE_ENV=development
LOG_LEVEL=debug

# .env.staging
PB_URL=https://staging-sanctuary.pockethost.io
NODE_ENV=staging
LOG_LEVEL=info

# .env.production
PB_URL=https://sanctuary-stream.pockethost.io
NODE_ENV=production
LOG_LEVEL=warn
```

### Loading Environments

```typescript
// sanctuary-bridge/src/config.ts
import dotenv from 'dotenv';
import { z } from 'zod';

// Load environment-specific file
const env = process.env.NODE_ENV || 'development';
const envFile = env === 'production' ? '.env.production' : '.env';
dotenv.config({ path: envFile });

// Validate with Zod
const ConfigSchema = z.object({
  PB_URL: z.string().url(),
  BRIDGE_EMAIL: z.string().email(),
  BRIDGE_PASS: z.string().min(8),
  OBS_URL: z.string().url(),
  OBS_PASS: z.string(),
  STREAM_ID: z.string(),
  LOG_LEVEL: z.enum(['debug', 'info', 'warn', 'error']),
  NODE_ENV: z.enum(['development', 'staging', 'production'])
});

export const config = ConfigSchema.parse(process.env);
```

