## 🎯 Schema Consistency Checklist

- [ ] Schema defined in `pocketbase/schema-init.js`
- [ ] Unique constraints on idempotency keys
- [ ] RBAC rules tested locally
- [ ] Test data created for local dev
- [ ] Schema export script in `package.json`
- [ ] Migration scripts for changes
- [ ] Zod schemas match database schema
- [ ] TypeScript types generated from Zod
- [ ] Integration tests verify schema
- [ ] Staging matches production schema

---

## 🐛 Debugging Tips

### PocketBase Issues

```bash
# Check PocketBase logs
tail -f pocketbase/local/pb_data/logs/*.log

# Test API directly
curl http://127.0.0.1:8090/api/health
curl -X POST http://127.0.0.1:8090/api/collections/users/auth-with-password \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"identity":"pastor@local.dev","password":"pastor123456"}'
```

### Bridge Service Issues

```bash
# Enable debug logging
LOG_LEVEL=debug npm run dev

# Test OBS connection
node -e "const OBS = require('obs-websocket-js').default; const obs = new OBS(); obs.connect('ws://127.0.0.1:4455', 'password').then(() => console.log('Connected')).catch(console.error);"
```

### Schema Validation

```typescript
// sanctuary-app/src/lib/validate-schema.ts
import { z } from 'zod';

export const CommandSchema = z.object({
  id: z.string(),
  action: z.enum(['START', 'STOP']),
  executed: z.boolean(),
  correlation_id: z.string().uuid(),
  payload: z.record(z.unknown()).optional(),
  created_by: z.string(),
  created: z.string().datetime(),
  updated: z.string().datetime()
});

// Use in components
const command = CommandSchema.parse(unknownData); // Throws if invalid
```

